author: COMSOL
description: This example solves a 3D model of a steam reformer serving a stationary fuel-cell unit with hydrogen. The tightly coupled system of mass, energy, and momentum equations used to describe the reformer is readily set up using the predefined physics interfaces of the Chemical Reaction Engineering Module.
